# StartMission — Phase 1 of the runtime action protocol.
#
# Sent: sim_supervisor_node → mission_control_node
#
# Carries the chosen mission. mission_control_node drives mode_manager
# to bring up the right lifecycle nodes with the right strategy flag,
# emits periodic heartbeats while configure/activate is in flight, and
# reports ready/failed at the end. Cancellable — switching mission
# during this window re-enters Phase 1 for the new mission without a
# full container restart.
#
# Once `ready=true` arrives, the supervisor opens a separate
# RuntimeControl action for Phase 2.

# ---------------- Goal ----------------
# Mission identifier. Must be one of:
#   "trackdrive" | "autocross" | "accel" | "skidpad"
string mission

---
# ---------------- Result ----------------
# True if all autonomy lifecycle nodes reached `active` inside the
# startup window; false if any failed to configure/activate.
bool ready

# Human-readable diagnostic when ready=false. Empty string on success.
string message

---
# ---------------- Feedback ----------------
# Heartbeat. mission_control_node emits one of these periodically so a
# crashed startup is detectable from the supervisor side without
# polling every lifecycle node directly.
#
# Stage values:
#   "configuring"  — mode_manager is calling change_state to configure
#   "activating"   — mode_manager is calling change_state to activate
#   "warming_up"   — autonomy nodes active; e.g. Numba JIT compile
#   "ready"        — all done, result imminent
string stage
builtin_interfaces/Time stamp
